","1261–1299":"1261–1299","1196–1227":"1196–1227","1204–Female":"1204–Overleden","1196":"1196","1262":"1262","1244 (age 28 1272)":"1244","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1282":"1282","1227":"1227","Bef 1262":"vóór 1262","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1204":"1204","1303":"1303","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1299":"1299","1244":"1244","Shardlow, Derbyshire, England":"Shardlow, Derbyshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","North Bovey, Devon, England":"North Bovey, Devon, England","Dunalamelin Castle, Ardee, Ireland":"Ardee, County Donegal, Ierland"},"en":{"1215–1282":"1215–1282","–1227":"–1227","1225–1262":"1225–1262","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1250–1299":"1250–1299","1261–1299":"1261–1299","1196–1227":"1196–1227","1204–Female":"1204–Deceased","1196":"1196","1262":"1262","1244 (age 28 1272)":"1244","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1282":"1282","1227":"1227","Bef 1262":"before 1262","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1204":"1204","1303":"1303","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1299":"1299","1244":"1244","Shardlow, Derbyshire, England":"Shardlow, Derbyshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","England":"England, United Kingdom","North Bovey, Devon, England":"North Bovey, Devon, England","Dunalamelin Castle, Ardee, Ireland":"Ardee, County Donegal, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Pipard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Lucien, Andre, Marcel, Emile, Michel, Normand, Adrien, Antoine, Benoit, Elzear, Fernand.","French, Walloon, Catalan, and German; Breton (also <b>Le Picard</b>): from Old French and Catalan <i>picard</i> ‘Picard’, a habitational name for someone from Picardy in northern France. This surname is also found in the Flemish part of Belgium. Compare   Pecore  .","French: in some cases, probably also from <i>pic</i> ‘pick, pike’ + the pejorative suffix <i>-ard</i>, applied as a nickname for e.g. a user of a pointed tool."],"variants":[{"name":"Picart","meanings":["French; Breton (rarely <b>Le Picart</b>): variant of   Picard  , especially in Brittany (Finistère).","Catalan: variant of   Picard  ."]},{"name":"Pecore","meanings":["Altered form of French   Picard  , reflecting the characteristic Canadian and American French rounding of the <i>-ard</i> ending."]},{"name":"Pickard","meanings":["English (mainly Yorkshire) and German: habitational name for someone from Picardy in northern France (see   Picard   1).","English: in some cases, possibly also from the Old French personal name <i>Picard</i>, probably from an ancient Germanic name, composed of the elements <i>bic</i> ‘sharp point, pointed weapon’ + <i>hard</i> ‘hardy, brave, strong’."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":0,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":9,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":44,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Pipard was born in 1215, in North Bovey, Devon, England, her father, William Pipard III, was 19 and her mother, Alda Auda Hereford, was 12. She had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Ralph FitzNicholas. She died in 1282, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1215–1282":"1215–1282","–1227":"–1227","1225–1262":"1225–1262","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1250–1299":"1250–1299","1261–1299":"1261–1299","1196–1227":"1196–1227","1204–Female":"1204–Surnud","1196":"1196","1262":"1262","1244 (age 28 1272)":"1244","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1282":"1282","1227":"1227","Bef 1262":"enne 1262","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1204":"1204","1303":"1303","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1299":"1299","1244":"1244","Shardlow, Derbyshire, England":"Shardlow, Derbyshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","North Bovey, Devon, England":"North Bovey, Devon, England","Dunalamelin Castle, Ardee, Ireland":"Ardee, County Donegal, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1215–1282":"1215–1282","–1227":"–1227","1225–1262":"1225–1262","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1250–1299":"1250–1299","1261–1299":"1261–1299","1196–1227":"1196–122